This is a bug reported as [SR-11494][1]. Stored type properties are supposed to be lazily initialized on their first access. As per the [Documentation][2]

However, in this case, when compiled with the optimization flag the stored Type property&#39;s initialization is called at compile-time.

You could change **someValue** to a Computed Type Properties, then it&#39;s only called at **runtime**.  

    class MainView: UIView {
       static var someValue: Int {
            print(&quot;some value init&quot;)
            return 1
        }
    }


  [1]: https://bugs.swift.org/browse/SR-11494
  [2]: https://docs.swift.org/swift-book/LanguageGuide/Properties.html

